ClamAV

Target IP: 192.168.152.42

Scanning


There are seven TCP ports open on the target machine.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP

The webpage above is displayed for this application. The title of the webpage Ph33r is interesting, as it could possibly be a username.


Coverting the binary to ASCII outputs the message ifyoudontpwnmeuran00b, as shown above. After performing directory search against this application, I did not find anything.

Port 25: SMTP

After Googling the version number of this application, I found it is vulnerable. CVE-2007-4560 is given for this vulnerability. Apparently the clamav-milter is vulnerable.

Exploitation & Flag



I downloaded the exploit above and executed it using perl 4761.pl 192.168.152.42. The output states the port at 31337 is open.


Then I connected to the port open by the exploit. Now I have a root shell ready. This challenge only contains one flag.
